        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <date>Tuesday the 4th day of<lb/> month <add>טבת</add></date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <date>1863-4?</date>
            </p>
            <p><sic>greeting</sic> to my beloved<lb/> win<add>?</add> friend <persName>Mr.
                    Isaac</persName><lb/> Finally, I came to a deci-<lb/>sion after
                investigating<lb/> the circumstances <del>right</del><lb/> on the place and in a
                    <add>?</add><lb/> way. I believe and hope that<lb/> we'll be able to stay
                there<lb/> for room and board and for<lb/> telephone calls we'll pay<lb/> (budget)
                and except this<lb/> we'll try to do what is only<lb/> possible with the only<lb/>
                aim not to bring illegitimate<lb/> children into the nation<lb/> of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">2</p>
            <p>trying legally and not<lb/> against the law, even<lb/> although it is with<lb/>
                regret <del>mo</del> that the<lb/> missing cann'<sic>t</sic> be<lb/> avoided.</p>
            <p>I would insist that<lb/> opinions for and against<lb/> shall be expressed before<lb/>
                the accident. <date>Monday</date><lb/> I'll see the gentleman for a couple of<lb/>
                hours &amp; come to a conclusion with<lb/> him. I hope to hear from you &amp;<lb/>
                you will hear from me &amp; you can<lb/> expect by news<add>?</add> from me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Your friend who</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">cherishes him expects him</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah, from the house Bondi</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
